- "Sprouted recently" and "growing" are metaphors for "recent cases" and "older cases" based on the episode date;
- "Top 10 ranks" and "beyond the top 10 ranks" refer to the ranking of cases within each age group based on the episode date.

- 'Confirmed' cases are those that have been verified through diagnostic testing or other methods;
- 'Resolved' cases are those where the patient has recovered or the case has been otherwise concluded;
- 'Outbreak type' can include categories such as 'Sporadic', 'Epidemic', etc., which describe the nature and scale of the outbreak.

- "Primary sources of infection" refer to the sources with the highest number of cases for each age group;
- "Total number of cases" includes all cases regardless of their outcome;
- "Resolved cases" are cases that have been fully addressed or closed;
- "Active cases" are ongoing or unresolved cases.

- "stands out like a sore thumb" means it is very noticeable or prominent;
