- "Hospitalization rate per 1,000 population" is calculated as (number of hospitalizations / population) * 1,000;
- "ICU admission rate per 1,000 population" is calculated as (number of ICU admissions / population) * 1,000;
- "Intubation rate per 1,000 population" is calculated as (number of intubations / population) * 1,000;
- "Severity rank" is determined by the hospitalization rate, with higher rates indicating more severe health issues.

sql:
SELECT status, AVG(reported_cases) AS avg_reported_cases
FROM outbreaks
GROUP BY status;
